text:
Jaime Rolando Rosenthal Oliva (5 May 1936 – 12 January 2019) was a Honduran politician. He was the third Vice President of Honduras from 1986 to 1989 and a member of National Congress of Honduras from 2002 to 2006.
Rosenthal died following a heart attack on 12 January 2019. He was 82 years old.
